  "text": "To define sample size, we assumed a medium to large effect size of .30, consistent with other studies in the field. As a result, setting alpha at .05, power at .80 with 3 groups the power calculation yielded a sample of 111 participants (37 in each group). In addition to conducting the formal G-Power analysis, based on previous research with this population (e.g., [CITATION_1] , a sample of 37 participants per group is more than adequate. As noted in footnote 1, we managed to recruit more repeat SH participants than anticipated.",
